Why: (1) the VPU sleep/wake handshake is broken on this silicon - wake after
sleep never completes - so the suspend/resume sleep and wake calls are skipped
(the vendor never uses them either). (2) Upstream allocates codec DMA from the
device's default (global CMA) path; this routes all codec DMA (DPB, WTL/display
buffers, vb_task) to the SoC's dedicated mmz reserved-memory region via
of_reserved_mem, keeping the codec working set out of general CMA.

